@startuml t_component_07_parser_edge_cases
title Component Diagram — Parser Edge Cases\n(ambiguous tokens, hide/remove active, left-to-right, boundary cases)

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' GLOBAL DIRECTIVES — grammar productions that affect the whole diagram
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

left to right direction

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    FontSize 11
}
skinparam component<<hide_test>> {
    BackgroundColor #FFE0B2
    BorderColor #E65100
}

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 1. AMBIGUOUS BRACKET CASES
'    [Name] vs component body [...] vs guard [condition] on arrow
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

' Standard bracket component declaration
[BracketComponent] as BC1

' Bracket with stereotype — <<>> immediately after ]
[StereotypedBracket] <<service>> as BC2

' Bracket with color
[ColoredBracket] as BC3 #B3E5FC

' Bracket where name contains spaces (requires quotes internally — actually
' PlantUML allows spaces in bracket names as a special case)
[Component With Internal Spaces] as BC4

' Keyword component with body using [...] — ambiguity with bracket component
component BC5 [
    Description line one
    Description line two
    Third line of description
]

' Keyword component with body AND stereotype
component BC6 <<service>> [
    Has both a stereotype
    and a multi-line body
]

' Keyword component with body AND alias AND color
component BC7 <<gateway>> #EDE7F6 [
    Full featured body component
    with all optional attributes
]

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 2. INTERFACE AMBIGUITY — () vs interface keyword
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

' Circle-paren with no space before quote
() "NoSpaceIface" as NSI

' Circle-paren with name that could be a keyword
() "component" as IFACE_NAMED_COMPONENT
() "interface" as IFACE_NAMED_INTERFACE
() "package" as IFACE_NAMED_PACKAGE

' Interface with stereotype that matches component stereotype
interface SameStereotype <<service>>
interface "Quoted Interface" as QIF <<provided>> #E8F5E9

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 3. ALIAS COLLISION EDGE CASES
'    Alias same as a PlantUML keyword
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

component "Test Component A" as note_alias
component "Test Component B" as left
component "Test Component C" as right
component "Test Component D" as up
component "Test Component E" as down

' These must parse correctly even though the aliases match direction keywords
note_alias --> left : alias=note_alias
left --> right : alias=left
right --> up : alias=right
up --> down : alias=up

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 4. ARROW LABEL EDGE CASES
'    Labels with special chars, brackets, stereotypes
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[ArrowSrc] as AS1
[ArrowTgt] as AT1

' Arrow where label contains [] — must not be mistaken for guard or body
AS1 --> AT1 : label with [brackets] inside
AS1 ..> AT1 : <<stereotype>> as label
AS1 --> AT1 : label: with colon
AS1 --> AT1 : "quoted label"
AS1 -[#FF0000]-> AT1 : colored [with brackets]
AS1 --> AT1 : label / with slash

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 5. TAG SYSTEM — active hide/remove/restore directives
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

component "Visible Alpha" as VA $alpha $shared
component "Visible Beta"  as VB $beta  $shared
component "Will Be Hidden" as WBH $hidden_tag
component "Also Hidden"    as AH $hidden_tag $alpha
component "Restored"       as RS $hidden_tag $restore_tag
component "Unlinked Component" as UNLINKED

VA --> VB : alpha-to-beta
VB --> RS : beta-to-restored

' Active directives — these are parsed and executed:
hide $hidden_tag
restore $restore_tag
' hide @unlinked   ← would hide UNLINKED; commented to keep diagram readable

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 6. DEEPLY NESTED CONTAINERS with left-to-right layout
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

package "Tier 1" as T1 #EEF2FF {
    [T1_A] as T1A
    [T1_B] as T1B

    package "Tier 2" as T2 #FFF8E1 {
        [T2_A] as T2A
        [T2_B] as T2B

        package "Tier 3" as T3 #E8F5E9 {
            [T3_A] as T3A
            [T3_B] as T3B

            package "Tier 4" as T4 #FCE4EC {
                [T4_A] as T4A
                [T4_B] as T4B
            }
        }
    }
}

T1A --> T2A : t1→t2
T2A --> T3A : t2→t3
T3A --> T4A : t3→t4
T4A --> T4B : within t4
T4B --> T3B : t4→t3 back
T3B --> T2B : t3→t2 back
T2B --> T1B : t2→t1 back

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 7. MIXED DECLARATION ORDER
'    Transitions declared before components (forward references)
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

component "Forward A" as FWD_A
component "Forward B" as FWD_B
[Forward C] as FWD_C

' Links between forward-declared components
FWD_A --> FWD_B : forward ref link
FWD_B ..> FWD_C : also forward

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 8. PORT EDGE CASES — port on bracket-form component
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

component "Port Test" as PT {
    port p1
    portin p2
    portout p3
    port "Quoted Port" as QP
    port "Port/With/Slashes" as PWS
}

p1 --> T1A : port to component
T2A --> p2 : component to portin
p3 --> FWD_A : portout to forward-ref
QP --> VB : quoted port link

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 9. MULTILINE COMPONENT NAMES IN BRACKET FORM
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[Line1\nLine2] as ML2
[Line1\nLine2\nLine3] as ML3
[A\nB\nC\nD] as ML4

ML2 --> ML3 : multi to multi
ML3 --> ML4

' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' 10. NOTES — edge cases
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

note right of BC5
    **Body component parser test:**
    The body after component keyword
    is a description body, NOT a bracket
    component declaration.
    Parser must context-disambiguate
    bracket vs body form.
end note

note right of T1
    **left to right direction:**
    Changes rankdir=LR in DOT output.
    Must be parsed as a global directive,
    not a transition or component name.
end note

note as EDGE_NOTE
    **Edge cases summary:**
    1. [body] vs [component] disambiguation
    2. () iface vs interface keyword
    3. Aliases matching keyword names
    4. Arrow labels containing []
    5. hide/remove/restore directives
    6. Forward references in transitions
    7. Port on keyword-form component
    8. Multiline \n in bracket names
    9. left to right direction directive
    10. allowmixing directive
end note

BC1 .. EDGE_NOTE

@enduml
